## Detailed Requirements Specification by Portal

This document outlines the detailed functional and non-functional requirements for the AI-First Personalized Learning Platform, broken down by portal in the specified development order: Admin Portal, Program Coordinator Portal, Teacher Portal, and Student Portal.

---

Okay, here are the added requirements for the Admin Portal, specifically addressing Educators/Teachers Management and Enrollment Management:

### 1. Admin Portal Requirements Specification (Updated)

**Goal:** To provide platform administrators with the necessary tools to manage the overall system, user accounts, programs, courses, AI agent configurations, system-level settings, educators, and enrollments.

**Target Users:** Platform Administrators

**Key Features:**

* User Management
* Program Management
* Course & Session Management
* AI Agent Configuration
* System Monitoring & Analytics
* Credit System Management
* Content Library Management
* Program Coordinator Management
* **Educators/Teachers Management**
* **Enrollment Management**

**Detailed Requirements (Functional):**

| ID     | Feature Area               | Requirement                                                                                                                                                                                                   | Priority |
| :------ | :------------------------- | :------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | :------- |
| AP-F1   | User Management          | The system must allow administrators to **create** new user accounts (students, educators, program coordinators, other admins) by providing necessary details (username, email, password, role).                | High     |
| AP-F2   | User Management          | The system must allow administrators to **read** (view) a list of all user accounts, including their roles and status.                                                                                       | High     |
| AP-F3   | User Management          | The system must allow administrators to **update** existing user account details, including roles and status.                                                                                                   | High     |
| AP-F4   | User Management          | The system must allow administrators to **delete** user accounts from the system.                                                                                                                              | High     |
| AP-F5   | User Management          | The system must allow administrators to filter and search user accounts based on criteria like role, name, or email.                                                                                           | Medium   |
| AP-F6   | Program Management         | The system must allow administrators to **create** new Programs by defining program name, description, learning objectives, and associating it with a Program Coordinator.                                 | High     |
| AP-F7   | Program Management         | The system must allow administrators to **read** (view) a list of all Programs and their details.                                                                                                           | High     |
| AP-F8   | Program Management         | The system must allow administrators to **update** existing Program details.                                                                                                                                | Medium   |
| AP-F9   | Program Management         | The system must allow administrators to **delete** Programs.                                                                                                                                              | Medium   |
| AP-F10  | Course & Session Mgmt    | The system must allow administrators to **create** new Courses, defining course name, description, associating it with a Program, and assigning educators.                                                    | High     |
| AP-F11  | Course & Session Mgmt    | The system must allow administrators to **read** (view) a list of all Courses and their details.                                                                                                           | High     |
| AP-F12  | Course & Session Mgmt    | The system must allow administrators to **update** existing Course details.                                                                                                                                | Medium   |
| AP-F13  | Course & Session Mgmt    | The system must allow administrators to **delete** Courses.                                                                                                                                              | Medium   |
| AP-F14  | Course & Session Mgmt    | The system must allow administrators to **create** new Sessions within a Course, defining schedule, capacity, and assigning educators.                                                                      | High     |
| AP-F15  | Course & Session Mgmt    | The system must allow administrators to **read** (view) a list of all Sessions and their details.                                                                                                         | High     |
| AP-F16  | Course & Session Mgmt    | The system must allow administrators to **update** existing Session details.                                                                                                                                | Medium   |
| AP-F17  | Course & Session Mgmt    | The system must allow administrators to **delete** Sessions.                                                                                                                                              | Medium   |
| AP-F18  | AI Agent Config          | The system must allow administrators to configure global parameters for AI agents, including base personalities, response styles (within predefined limits), and default access to knowledge bases.       | Medium   |
| AP-F19  | AI Agent Config          | The system must allow administrators to monitor the overall performance and usage statistics of AI agents.                                                                                                  | Medium   |
| AP-F20  | System Monitoring        | The system must provide administrators with a dashboard displaying key platform usage statistics (e.g., number of active users, content uploads, AI interactions).                                       | Medium   |
| AP-F21  | System Monitoring        | The system must provide administrators with tools to monitor the performance of the platform infrastructure and identify potential technical issues.                                                      | High     |
| AP-F22  | Credit System Mgmt       | The system must allow administrators to manage the global credit system, including setting initial credit balances for new users and configuring credit costs for AI interactions.                         | Medium   |
| AP-F23  | Credit System Mgmt       | The system must allow administrators to view reports on credit usage across the platform.                                                                                                                     | Low      |
| AP-F24  | Content Library Mgmt     | The system must provide a centralized repository for all learning content (documents, videos, etc.).                                                                                                       | Medium   |
| AP-F25  | Content Library Mgmt     | The system must allow administrators to upload, categorize, and tag content in the content library.                                                                                                          | Medium   |
| AP-F26  | Content Library Mgmt     | The system must allow administrators to manage access permissions for content in the library.                                                                                                                 | Low      |
| AP-F27  | Program Coordinator Mgmt | The system must allow administrators to **create** new Program Coordinator accounts.                                                                                                                       | High     |
| AP-F28  | Program Coordinator Mgmt | The system must allow administrators to **read** (view) a list of all Program Coordinators and their assigned Programs.                                                                                  | High     |
| AP-F29  | Program Coordinator Mgmt | The system must allow administrators to **update** Program Coordinator details and their assigned Programs.                                                                                                | Medium   |
| AP-F30  | Program Coordinator Mgmt | The system must allow administrators to **delete** Program Coordinator accounts.                                                                                                                           | Medium   |
| **AP-F31** | **Educators/Teachers Mgmt** | The system must allow administrators to **read** (view) a list of all educator accounts, including their assigned Courses and Programs.                                                                  | High     |
| **AP-F32** | **Educators/Teachers Mgmt** | The system must allow administrators to **update** educator account details, including their assigned Courses and Programs.                                                                             | Medium   |
| **AP-F33** | **Educators/Teachers Mgmt** | The system must allow administrators to **assign** and **unassign** educators from specific Courses and Sessions.                                                                                        | High     |
| **AP-F34** | **Educators/Teachers Mgmt** | The system must allow administrators to filter and search educator accounts based on criteria like name, email, or assigned Courses/Programs.                                                            | Medium   |
| **AP-F35** | **Enrollment Management**  | The system must allow administrators to **read** (view) a list of all student enrollments in Programs, Courses, and Sessions.                                                                          | High     |
| **AP-F36** | **Enrollment Management**  | The system must allow administrators to **manually enroll** students into specific Programs, Courses, and Sessions.                                                                                    | High     |
| **AP-F37** | **Enrollment Management**  | The system must allow administrators to **manually unenroll** students from specific Programs, Courses, and Sessions.                                                                                  | High     |
| **AP-F38** | **Enrollment Management**  | The system must allow administrators to view enrollment statistics and reports for Programs, Courses, and Sessions.                                                                                   | Medium   |
| **AP-F39** | **Enrollment Management**  | The system should allow administrators to manage waiting lists for Sessions that are at full capacity (if this feature is implemented).                                                              | Low      |
| **AP-F40** | **Enrollment Management**  | The system should allow administrators to bulk enroll or unenroll students using CSV files or similar methods.                                                                                         | Low      |

**Non-Functional Requirements:**

* **AP-NF1: Security:** The Admin Portal must be secured with strong authentication and authorization mechanisms to prevent unauthorized access.
* **AP-NF2: Performance:** The Admin Portal should be responsive and provide quick access to information and functionalities.
* **AP-NF3: Usability:** The Admin Portal should have a clear, intuitive, and user-friendly interface for efficient management.
* **AP-NF4: Auditability:** All administrative actions performed within the Admin Portal must be logged for audit purposes.
* **AP-NF5: Reliability:** The Admin Portal must be reliable and available as needed.

These additions provide the necessary administrative capabilities for managing educators and student enrollments, ensuring comprehensive control over the platform's user base and program participation.


---

### 2. Program Coordinator Portal Requirements Specification

**Goal:** To provide Program Coordinators with the tools to manage their assigned Programs, including curriculum oversight, content approval, educator management, and performance monitoring.

**Target Users:** Program Coordinators

**Key Features:**

* Dashboard Overview
* Program Management
* Content Management & Approval
* Educator Management
* Reporting & Analytics
* Communication Tools
* Program Academic Calendar Management

**Detailed Requirements (Functional):**

| ID     | Feature Area               | Requirement                                                                                                                                                                                            | Priority |
| :----- | :------------------------- | :----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | :------- |
| PCP-F1 | Dashboard Overview         | The portal must display an overview of assigned programs, key performance indicators (enrollment, completion rates), content approval queue, and educator activity summaries.                       | High     |
| PCP-F2 | Program Management         | The system must allow Program Coordinators to **read** (view) detailed information about their assigned Programs, including objectives, curriculum structure, enrolled students, and associated educators. | High     |
| PCP-F3 | Program Management         | The system must allow Program Coordinators to review the structure of their assigned Programs to ensure alignment with educational goals and standards.                                            | High     |
| PCP-F4 | Program Management         | The system must allow Program Coordinators to **approve** or **reject** entire Programs, controlling their publishing and availability to students.                                                     | High     |
| PCP-F5 | Program Management         | The system must allow Program Coordinators to **read** (view) the subject sequencing and Course structure within their assigned Programs.                                                               | High     |
| PCP-F6 | Program Management         | The system must allow Program Coordinators to provide feedback and recommendations to educators regarding curriculum structure within their assigned Programs.                                      | Medium   |
| PCP-F7 | Program Management         | The system must allow Program Coordinators to monitor key performance indicators for their assigned Programs and identify areas needing improvement.                                                   | Medium   |
| PCP-F8 | Content Mgmt & Approval    | The system must provide an interface for Program Coordinators to view submitted interactive readings, quizzes, flashcards, and other activities for Courses within their assigned Programs.           | High     |
| PCP-F9 | Content Mgmt & Approval    | The system must allow Program Coordinators to **approve** or **reject** submitted content, ensuring quality, accuracy, and alignment with learning objectives.                                       | High     |
| PCP-F10 | Content Mgmt & Approval    | The system must allow Program Coordinators to provide specific feedback to educators on rejected content, suggesting improvements.                                                                     | High     |
| PCP-F11 | Content Mgmt & Approval    | The system must allow Program Coordinators to review and approve new documents or updates to the vector database (RAG) for their assigned Programs.                                                 | High     |
| PCP-F12 | Content Mgmt & Approval    | The system must allow Program Coordinators to monitor the performance of the RAG system within their assigned Programs.                                                                              | Medium   |
| PCP-F13 | Educator Management        | The system must allow Program Coordinators to **read** (view) a list of educators contributing to Courses within their assigned Programs.                                                            | High     |
| PCP-F14 | Educator Management        | The system must allow Program Coordinators to monitor educator activity, including content creation, feedback provided to students, and overall engagement within their assigned Programs.         | Medium   |
| PCP-F15 | Educator Management        | The system must allow Program Coordinators to provide feedback and guidance to educators to improve their content and teaching practices within their assigned Programs.                             | Medium   |
| PCP-F16 | Educator Management        | The system should allow Program Coordinators to approve or reject educator applications to contribute to specific Programs (if this functionality is implemented).                                 | Low      |
| PCP-F17 | Reporting & Analytics      | The system must provide Program Coordinators with detailed reports on student progress, engagement, and completion rates within their assigned Programs.                                             | High     |
| PCP-F18 | Reporting & Analytics      | The system must provide Program Coordinators with reports analyzing the effectiveness of content within their assigned Programs.                                                                    | Medium   |
| PCP-F19 | Reporting & Analytics      | The system must provide Program Coordinators with reports on educator performance within their assigned Programs.                                                                                 | Low      |
| PCP-F20 | Communication Tools        | The system must allow Program Coordinators to send direct messages to educators within their assigned Programs.                                                                                     | High     |
| PCP-F21 | Communication Tools        | The system must allow Program Coordinators to make announcements to students enrolled in their assigned Programs.                                                                                    | Medium   |
| PCP-F22 | Program Academic Calendar  | The system must allow Program Coordinators to **create** and manage the academic calendar for their assigned Programs, including defining key dates, holidays, and deadlines.                      | High     |
| PCP-F23 | Program Academic Calendar  | The system must allow Program Coordinators to **read** (view) the academic calendar for their assigned Programs.                                                                                  | High     |

**Non-Functional Requirements:**

* **PCP-NF1: Security:** The Program Coordinator Portal must be secured with appropriate authentication and authorization mechanisms.
* **PCP-NF2: Performance:** The Program Coordinator Portal should be responsive and provide efficient access to program-related information.
* **PCP-NF3: Usability:** The Program Coordinator Portal should have a clear and intuitive interface for managing program activities.
* **PCP-NF4: Reliability:** The Program Coordinator Portal must be reliable and available as needed.

---

### 3. Teacher Portal Requirements Specification

**Goal:** To provide educators with the tools to manage their assigned Courses and Sessions, create and manage content, interact with students, and monitor student progress.

**Target Users:** Educators

**Key Features:**

* Dashboard Overview
* Course & Session Management
* Content Authoring & Management
* Student Management
* Progress Monitoring & Analytics
* Communication Tools
* RAG Knowledge Base Contribution

**Detailed Requirements (Functional):**

| ID     | Feature Area               | Requirement                                                                                                                                                                                           | Priority |
| :----- | :------------------------- | :---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | :------- |
| TP-F1  | Dashboard Overview         | The portal must display an overview of assigned Courses and Sessions, student progress summaries, and communication notifications.                                                                 | High     |
| TP-F2  | Course & Session Mgmt      | The system must allow educators to **read** (view) details of their assigned Courses and Sessions.                                                                                                   | High     |
| TP-F3  | Course & Session Mgmt      | The system must allow educators to manage their Session schedules and availability (if applicable).                                                                                                   | Medium   |
| TP-F4  | Content Authoring & Mgmt   | The system must provide educators with tools to create interactive readings, including embedding examples and AI assistance prompts.                                                               | High     |
| TP-F5  | Content Authoring & Mgmt   | The system must provide educators with tools to create quizzes with various question types.                                                                                                          | High     |
| TP-F6  | Content Authoring & Mgmt   | The system must provide educators with tools to create flashcard decks for their Courses.                                                                                                          | Medium   |
| TP-F7  | Content Authoring & Mgmt   | The system must allow educators to upload and manage learning resources (documents, videos, etc.) for their Courses.                                                                               | High     |
| TP-F8  | Content Authoring & Mgmt   | The system must allow educators to submit authored content for review and approval by the Program Coordinator.                                                                                       | High     |
| TP-F9  | Student Management         | The system must allow educators to **read** (view) profiles of students enrolled in their Courses and Sessions.                                                                                         | High     |
| TP-F10 | Student Management         | The system must allow educators to communicate with individual students or groups of students within their Courses and Sessions via direct messaging.                                                   | High     |
| TP-F11 | Student Management         | The system must allow educators to provide feedback on student assignments and activities within their Courses.                                                                                      | High     |
| TP-F12 | Student Management         | The system should allow educators to adjust individual student learning paths or recommend specific activities within their Courses (with appropriate permissions).                                  | Medium   |
| TP-F13 | Progress Monitoring & Analytics | The system must provide educators with detailed reports on student progress and performance within their Courses and Sessions.                                                                     | High     |
| TP-F14 | Progress Monitoring & Analytics | The system must provide educators with analytics on the effectiveness of their content within their Courses.                                                                                       | Medium   |
| TP-F15 | Communication Tools        | The system must allow educators to send announcements to students enrolled in their Courses and Sessions.                                                                                             | High     |
| TP-F16 | RAG Knowledge Base Contrib | The system must allow educators to contribute to the subject knowledge base (RAG) for their Courses by uploading relevant documents and providing descriptions.                                     | High     |
| TP-F17 | RAG Knowledge Base Contrib | The system must provide educators with guidelines and best practices for contributing to the knowledge base.                                                                                         | Medium   |

**Non-Functional Requirements:**

* **TP-NF1: Security:** The Teacher Portal must be secured to protect student data and prevent unauthorized access to course materials.
* **TP-NF2: Performance:** The Teacher Portal should be responsive and allow for efficient content creation and student management.
* **TP-NF3: Usability:** The Teacher Portal should have an intuitive interface that is easy for educators to use for their daily tasks.
* **TP-NF4: Reliability:** The Teacher Portal must be reliable and available for educators to manage their courses effectively.

---

### 4. Student Portal Requirements Specification

**Goal:** To provide students with a personalized and engaging learning environment where they can access course materials, interact with AI tutors, track their progress, and participate in gamified activities.

**Target Users:** Students

**Key Features:**

* Personalized Dashboard
* Program & Course Access
* Session Management
* AI Tutor Interaction
* Activity Hub
* Personalized Learning Path
* Scheduler & Goal Setting
* Program Academic Calendar
* Progress Tracking & Analytics
* Communication Tools
* Leaderboards & Badges

**Detailed Requirements (Functional):**

| ID     | Feature Area              | Requirement                                                                                                                                                                                               | Priority |
| :----- | :------------------------ | :-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | :------- |
| SP-F1  | Personalized Dashboard    | The portal must display a personalized welcome message, learning path progress, upcoming activities, AI agent recommendations, and goal tracking.                                                          | High     |
| SP-F2  | Program & Course Access   | The system must allow students to browse available Programs and enroll in them.                                                                                                                            | High     |
| SP-F3  | Program & Course Access   | The system must allow students to view the Courses they are enrolled in within their Programs.                                                                                                              | High     |
| SP-F4  | Session Management        | The system must allow students to view details of their assigned Sessions within a Course, including schedule and educator.                                                                               | High     |
| SP-F5  | AI Tutor Interaction      | The system must provide a dedicated chat interface for students to interact with AI agents.                                                                                                                 | High     |
| SP-F6  | AI Tutor Interaction      | The system must allow students to select specific AI agents for different learning needs.                                                                                                                 | Medium   |
| SP-F7  | AI Tutor Interaction      | The system should provide contextual AI assistance based on the student's current activity-subject-course context.                                                                                                               | Medium   |
| SP-F8  | Activity Hub              | The system must allow students to access and participate in quizzes, openpended quizzes and live quizzes within their Courses.                                                                                                                | High     |
| SP-F9  | Activity Hub              | The system must allow students to access and utilize personalized flashcards for their Courses.                                                                                                           | Medium   |
| SP-F10 | Activity Hub              | The system must allow students to access and interact with interactive readings, including utilizing AI assistance for explanations.                                                                     | High     |
| SP-F11 | Activity Hub              | The system must allow students to submit assignments for their Courses.                                                                                                                                 | High     |
| SP-F12 | Activity Hub              | The system must allow students to participate in gamified activities and view their progress.                                                                                                             | Medium   |
| SP-F13 | Personalized Learning Path | The system must display the AI-generated learning path for each Course.                                                                                                                                  | High     |
| SP-F14 | Personalized Learning Path | The system should allow students to customize their learning path within Courses to some extent (e.g., prioritize topics).                                                                             | Medium   |
| SP-F15 | Scheduler & Goal Setting    | The system must allow students to schedule study sessions and set reminders.                                                                                                                              | Medium   |
| SP-F16 | Scheduler & Goal Setting    | The system must allow students to set learning goals for individual Courses and the overall Program.                                                                                                    | Medium   |
| SP-F17 | Program Academic Calendar | The system must allow students to view the academic calendar for their enrolled Program.                                                                                                                  | High     |
| SP-F18 | Progress Tracking & Analytics | The system must display the student's progress within each Course.                                                                                                                                    | High     |
| SP-F19 | Progress Tracking & Analytics | The system must track and display the student's skill mastery within Courses.                                                                                                                            | Medium   |
| SP-F20 | Progress Tracking & Analytics | The system must display the student's performance history on quizzes and assignments.                                                                                                                  | High     |
| SP-F21 | Communication Tools       | The system must allow students to send direct messages to their educators within specific Courses.                                                                                                     | High     |
| SP-F22 | Communication Tools       | The system should provide access to optional forum or community features for each Course.                                                                                                               | Low      |
| SP-F23 | Leaderboards & Badges     | The system must display leaderboards for Courses and potentially Programs.                                                                                                                               | Medium   |
| SP-F24 | Leaderboards & Badges     | The system must display the badges and points earned by the student through gamified activities.                                                                                                         | Medium   |

**Non-Functional Requirements:**

* **SP-NF1: Security:** The Student Portal must be secure to protect student data and privacy.
* **SP-NF2: Performance:** The Student Portal should be responsive and provide a smooth learning experience.
* **SP-NF3: Usability:** The Student Portal should have an intuitive and engaging interface that is easy for students to navigate.
* **SP-NF4: Accessibility:** The Student Portal should be accessible to students with disabilities, adhering to accessibility guidelines.
* **SP-NF5: Reliability:** The Student Portal must be reliable and available for students to access their learning materials and activities.
